---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL
---
<Layout title="ReqForge — Getting Started">
  <div class="container" style="display: flex; gap: 3rem;">
    <nav class="doc-sidebar">
      <h4>Getting Started</h4>
      <a href={`${base}docs/getting-started`} class="active">Installation & Quickstart</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/collections`}>Collections & Requests</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/environments`}>Environments & Variables</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/auth`}>Authentication</a>
      <h4>Guides</h4>
      <a href={`${base}docs/testing`}>Testing & Scripts</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/import-export`}>Importing & Exporting</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/plugins`}>Plugin Development</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/sync`}>Cloud Sync</a>
      <h4>Reference</h4>
      <a href={`${base}docs/cli`}>CLI Reference</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/keyboard`}>Keyboard Shortcuts</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/troubleshooting`}>Troubleshooting</a>
    </nav>
    <article class="doc-content">
      <h1>Installation & Quickstart</h1>

      <h2>Desktop App</h2>
      <p>Download the latest release for your platform from <a href="https://github.com/reqforge/reqforge/releases">GitHub Releases</a>.</p>
      <pre># macOS
curl -sSL https://github.com/reqforge/reqforge/releases/latest/download/reqforge-aarch64-apple-darwin.tar.gz | tar -xz

# Linux
curl -sSL https://github.com/reqforge/reqforge/releases/latest/download/reqforge-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.xz | tar -xJ

# Windows
# Download the .zip and extract</pre>

      <h2>CLI</h2>
      <p>The CLI is bundled with the desktop app, or you can download it separately:</p>
      <pre># Run a request
reqforge run https://api.example.com/users

# Validate a collection
reqforge validate -w ~/workspace

# List collections
reqforge list -w ~/workspace

# Search the plugin marketplace
reqforge plugin search logging --tag logging</pre>

      <h2>Quick Tour</h2>
      <p>When you open ReqForge for the first time, you'll see:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>URL Bar</strong> — type your request URL and select the HTTP method</li>
        <li><strong>Params / Headers / Body</strong> — tabs to configure each part of the request</li>
        <li><strong>Send button</strong> — executes the request</li>
        <li><strong>Response panel</strong> — shows status, headers, body, and timing</li>
        <li><strong>Command palette</strong> — Ctrl+K to search and run commands</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
